<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[498,1542,1694,1922]" lastBlockId="22.[498,1542,234,779]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[725,876,1737,1763]" pageId="21" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
is strongly supported, but the number of tribes included in this subfamily is still unclear. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sihvonen P &amp; Mutanen M &amp; Kaila L &amp; Brehm G &amp; Hausmann A &amp; Staude HS" box="[883,1136,1776,1803]" journalOrPublisher="PLOS ONE" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="20356" part="6" refId="ref20700" refString="Sihvonen P, Mutanen M, Kaila L, Brehm G, Hausmann A, Staude HS. 2011. Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). PLOS ONE 6 (6): e 20356 DOI 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0020356." title="Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae)" type="journal article" year="2011">
<emphasis box="[883,1136,1776,1803]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg, 2019" authorityName="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[883,988,1776,1802]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" status="new subfamily" subFamily="Sihvonen">Sihvonen</taxonomicName>
et al. (2011)
</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
analyzed 27 species assigned to 11 tribes, followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[760,955,1816,1842]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[760,955,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
with 116 species in 12 tribes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[1312,1508,1816,1842]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[1312,1508,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized nine tribes, and validated the monophyly of 12 tribes, with two new tribes Ornithospilini and Agathiini being the first two clades branching off the main lineage of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[498,652,234,260]" pageId="22" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
. Our study (168 species) validates the monophyly of 13 tribes, eleven of which were defined in previous studies: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Ban et al." authorityYear="2018" box="[972,1107,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hemitheini">Hemitheini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1895" box="[1120,1265,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysphaniini">Dysphaniini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[1278,1456,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1465,1517,275,300]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">s.str.</emphasis>
, Ornithospilini, Agathiini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[804,924,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aracimini">Aracimini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[937,1123,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neohipparchini">Neohipparchini</taxonomicName>
, Timandromorphini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[1381,1517,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Geometrini">Geometrini</taxonomicName>
, Comibaeini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[649,773,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini</taxonomicName>
. One synonymization is proposed: 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferguson, 1969" authorityName="Ferguson" authorityYear="1969" box="[1190,1511,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synchlorini">Synchlorini Ferguson, 1969</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[498,607,394,420]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">syn. nov.</emphasis>
is synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gumppenberg, 1887" authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[867,1240,394,420]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini Gumppenberg, 1887</taxonomicName>
. One tribe is proposed as new: 
<taxonomicName authority="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg, 2019" authorityName="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[561,781,433,459]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="trib. nov." tribe="Chlorodontoperini">Chlorodontoperini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,903,433,460]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[790,903,433,460]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="tribe">trib. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and one tribe (
<taxonomicName authority="Viidalepp, 1981" authorityName="Viidalepp" authorityYear="1981" box="[1093,1469,433,460]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Archaeobalbini">Archaeobalbini Viidalepp, 1981</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">stat. rev.</emphasis>
) is raised from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[923,1104,473,499]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[498,1542,234,779]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[530,725,513,539]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[530,725,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
found that 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren, 1894" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1894" box="[867,1182,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ornithospila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,1012,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ornithospila</emphasis>
Warren, 1894
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the rest of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[498,651,553,579]" pageId="22" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee, 1858" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" box="[717,977,553,580]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Agathia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[717,809,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Agathia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Guenee A." box="[817,977,553,580]" journalOrPublisher="Tom IX. X. Uranides et Phalenites I" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="304" part="II" refId="ref18551" refString="Guenee A. 1858. Histoire naturelle des insectes (Lepidoptera), Species General des Lepidopteres. Tom IX. X. Uranides et Phalenites I. II. Paris: Roret, 304." title="Histoire naturelle des insectes (Lepidoptera), Species General des Lepidopteres" type="journal article" year="1858">Guenée, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the rest of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1242,1393,553,579]" pageId="22" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
minus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1894" box="[498,643,593,619]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ornithospila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,643,593,619]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ornithospila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although weakly supported, our results (with more species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" box="[1393,1485,593,619]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Agathia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1393,1485,593,619]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Agathia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sampled) placed Ornisthospilini+Agathiini together and these tribes are the sister to the rest of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[575,729,673,699]" pageId="22" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[739,934,673,699]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[739,934,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed as an isolated lineage as shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
. Given that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[720,915,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,915,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly forms an independent and well-supported lineage we propose the description of a new tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[1088,1311,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Chlorodontoperini">Chlorodontoperini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
